OVERVIEW -

This project is a web scraper that extracts information dynamically from websites. It allows users to input a URL and fetch relevant data, such as genres and summaries from websites. The scraper uses Scrapy for web crawling and Selenium for testing. The frontend is built with React, while the backend is implemented using Flask.

Features -

Allows users to input any website URL to extract and display information dynamically.

Uses Scrapy for efficient web crawling.

Employs Selenium for automated testing.

Built with React (frontend) and Flask (backend).

Technologies Used -

Frontend: React, JavaScript, HTML, CSS

Backend: Flask, Python

Web Scraping: Scrapy, BeautifulSoup

Testing: Selenium

Development Environment: VS Code

Installation -

Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed on your system:

Python 3.x

Node.js and npm

Virtual environment (optional but recommended)

ChromeDriver (for Selenium)
